# Project Development Rules

## Project Overview

This is a Next.js 14+ portfolio website with a developer tools hub.
- Framework: Next.js 14+ with App Router
- Language: TypeScript (strict mode)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS with custom theme
- Animations: Framer Motion
- Fonts: Inter (sans), Fira Code (mono)

### Key Files
- src/styles/brand-theme.js - Design system tokens
- src/components/ui/ - Reusable UI components
- STYLE_GUIDE.md - Usage guidelines
- tailwind.config.js - Extended Tailwind configuration

## Coding Standards & Naming Conventions

### File Naming

| Type | Convention | Examples |
|------|------------|----------|
| Components | PascalCase | `Button.tsx`, `Navbar.tsx`, `ProjectCard.tsx` |
| Hooks | camelCase with `use` prefix | `useGSAP.ts`, `useMagnetic.ts`, `useReducedMotion.ts` |
| Utilities | camelCase | `generateGradient.ts`, `animations.ts`, `seo.ts` |
| Types | camelCase | `animations.ts`, `tools.ts` (in src/types/) |
| Config | camelCase | `constants.ts`, `tools.ts` |
| Data | camelCase | `personal.ts`, `projects.ts`, `skills.ts` |
| Barrel exports | `index.ts` | Always use `index.ts` for re-exports |

### Folder Naming

| Type | Convention | Examples |
|------|------------|----------|
| Route segments | kebab-case | `gradient-generator/`, `json-to-typescript/` |
| Feature folders | camelCase | `animations/`, `backgrounds/`, `effects/` |
| Component groups | camelCase | `ui/`, `layout/`, `sections/` |

### Code Naming

| Type | Convention | Examples |
|------|------------|----------|
| Components | PascalCase | `Button`, `Navbar`, `AnimatedBackground` |
| Interfaces/Types | PascalCase | `ButtonProps`, `AnimationConfig`, `Tool` |
| Type aliases | PascalCase | `ButtonVariant`, `ToolCategory` |
| Functions | camelCase | `getButtonClasses`, `createScrollAnimation` |
| Variables | camelCase | `isMenuOpen`, `scrollProgress`, `reduceMotion` |
| Constants (objects) | camelCase | `toolCategories`, `navLinks`, `brandTheme` |
| Boolean variables | `is/has/should` prefix | `isActive`, `hasError`, `shouldAnimate` |
| Event handlers | `handle` prefix | `handleClick`, `handleSubmit`, `handleScroll` |
| Callbacks (props) | `on` prefix | `onClick`, `onChange`, `onComplete` |

### Component Structure

```tsx
'use client'; // Only if needed

import { useState } from 'react';
import Link from 'next/link';
// External imports first, then internal imports
import { Button } from '@/components/ui';
import brandTheme from '@/styles/brand-theme';

// Types at the top, after imports
interface ComponentProps {
  title: string;
  isActive?: boolean;
  onAction?: () => void;
}

// Helper functions before component
function helperFunction() {}

// Main component
export default function ComponentName({ title, isActive = false, onAction }: ComponentProps) {
  const [state, setState] = useState(false);
  
  const handleClick = () => {
    onAction?.();
  };

  return (
    <div>
      {/* JSX */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Export Patterns

- **Components**: Use default exports
  ```tsx
  export default function Button() {}
  // or
  const Button = forwardRef(...);
  Button.displayName = 'Button';
  export default Button;
  ```

- **Types**: Use named exports alongside component
  ```tsx
  export type ButtonVariant = 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'ghost';
  export interface ButtonProps { ... }
  export default Button;
  ```

- **Barrel exports (index.ts)**: Re-export defaults and types
  ```tsx
  export { default as Button } from './Button';
  export type { ButtonProps, ButtonVariant } from './Button';
  ```

- **Hooks**: Use named exports
  ```tsx
  export function useGSAP() { ... }
  // In index.ts
  export { useGSAP } from './useGSAP';
  ```

- **Utilities**: Use named exports
  ```tsx
  export function getToolById(id: string) { ... }
  export function searchTools(query: string) { ... }
  ```

### Import Order

1. React imports
2. Next.js imports
3. External library imports
4. Internal absolute imports (`@/...`)
5. Relative imports
6. Style imports
7. Type-only imports (if separated)

```tsx
import { useState, useEffect, useCallback } from 'react';
import Link from 'next/link';
import { motion } from 'framer-motion';
import { Button, Input } from '@/components/ui';
import { useGSAP } from '@/hooks';
import { helperFunction } from '../utils';
import styles from './Component.module.css';
```

### Path Aliases

Always use path aliases for imports outside the current directory:
- `@/components/*` - Components
- `@/hooks/*` - Custom hooks  
- `@/lib/*` - Library code (animations, data, utils)
- `@/types/*` - TypeScript types
- `@/styles/*` - Style files
- `@/config/*` - Configuration files

## Generic UI Components (ALWAYS USE THESE)

### Button Component
ALWAYS use the Button component from `@/components/ui` for buttons and button-like links.

```tsx
import { Button } from '@/components/ui';

// Variants: 'primary' | 'secondary' | 'ghost'
// Sizes: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg'

// As button
<Button variant="primary" size="lg">Submit</Button>

// As internal link (Next.js Link)
<Button href="/contact" variant="secondary" size="md">Contact</Button>

// As external link
<Button href="https://github.com" external variant="ghost" size="md">GitHub</Button>
```

### Form Components
ALWAYS use form components from `@/components/ui` for form elements.

```tsx
import { Input, Select, Textarea } from '@/components/ui';

// Input with label and error
<Input
  label="Email"
  type="email"
  name="email"
  error={errors.email}
  helperText="We'll never share your email"
/>

// Select with options
<Select
  label="Category"
  name="category"
  placeholder="Select an option"
  options={[
    { value: 'general', label: 'General Inquiry' },
    { value: 'support', label: 'Support' },
  ]}
  error={errors.category}
/>

// Textarea
<Textarea
  label="Message"
  name="message"
  rows={5}
  placeholder="Your message..."
  error={errors.message}
/>
```

## Theme and Styling Rules

