- Scale: hover:scale-105
- Card lift: hover:translate-y-[-4px]

### Framer Motion
- Use for scroll-triggered animations and page transitions
- Always respect prefers-reduced-motion

## Code Quality Rules

### TypeScript
- No any types without justification
- Define interfaces for all props
- Place shared types in src/types/
- Use type inference where possible, explicit types for function parameters and returns

### File Organization
- Portfolio routes: src/app/(portfolio)/
- Tools routes: src/app/(tools)/tools/
- Shared UI components: src/components/ui/
- Tool-specific components: src/components/tools/
- Custom hooks: src/hooks/
- Utilities: src/lib/utils/
- Data files: src/lib/data/
- Animation utilities: src/lib/animations/

## Accessibility Rules

- All interactive elements must have focus-visible states
- Use semantic HTML (nav, main, section, article)
- Include aria-label for icon-only buttons
- Ensure WCAG AA contrast (4.5:1)

### Focus States
focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-cyan-400 focus-visible:ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-slate-900

## Git Commit Rules

Use conventional commits:
- feat: New feature
- fix: Bug fix
- chore: Maintenance
- docs: Documentation
- refactor: Code refactoring
- style: Code style changes (formatting, etc.)
- test: Adding tests
- perf: Performance improvements

## Donts

- DONT use raw `<button>`, `<a>`, or `<Link>` for buttons - use the Button component
- DONT use raw `<input>`, `<select>`, `<textarea>` for forms - use Input, Select, Textarea components
- DONT use colors outside the theme
- DONT use any type in TypeScript
- DONT skip focus-visible states
- DONT use inline styles
- DONT use px units for spacing (use Tailwind spacing scale)
- DONT duplicate button/input styling - extend brandTheme.js instead
- DONT use default exports for hooks or utilities (use named exports)
- DONT mix naming conventions (stick to the patterns above)
- DONT create files with spaces in names
- DONT use SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE for constants (use camelCase)
